CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 28, 1951, pg. 11, reads: "Jabberwocky Jabberwock...was truly gay this year with A. Leo Weil School housing the amusing annual event presented by Delta Sigma Theta sorors. Pictured are, left: 'Miss Jabberwock,' Norma Lee, complete with crown and roses... - Harris Photos."  Article reads: "AKAs Capture First Prize in Jabberwock - Curiousity [Curiosity]? Yes, that was the theme of the Delta Sigma Theta's first Jabberwock in five years and it was a tremendous comeback.  The affair was held Friday, April 20 and was a night of fun and laughter for Pittsburghers...."
TitMainTitle: Man wearing tuxedo standing next to "Miss Jabberwock" Norma Lee wearing crown and holding bouquet, with other women in background, on stage at A. Leo Weil School, for Delta Sigma Theta's Jabberwock
